/*	The physical outlay of where photons can travel. Since     */
/*	this model is a plane parallel model, the only relevant    */
/*	coordinates are the z coordinates (in meters).             */
/*                                                                 */
/* [zm] Lowest elevation in the simulation (in meters).            */
/*	                                                           */
/* [zp] Highest elevation in the simulation (in meters).           */
/*	                                                           */
/* [gridnum] Number of individual layers in the atmosphere.        */
/*                                                                 */
/* The number of layer bounding planes in the simulation is        */
/* equal to (gridnum+1).  Each bounding plane must have the        */
/* following information attached to it                            */
/*                                                                 */
/*	1) [number] index,                                         */
/*                                                                 */
/*	2) [grid]   height of the bounding plane (in meters),      */
/*                                                                 */
/*	3) [rtflag] flag to indicate whether (1) or not (0) to     */
/*		    calculate fluxes and radiances at this plane.  */
/*                                                                 */
/*-----------------------------------------------------------------*/

[zm] LOWEST  ELEVATION FOR PHOTONS (in meters): 0.,
[zp] HIGHEST ELEVATION FOR PHOTONS (in meters): 45000.,

[gridnum] NUMBER OF ATMOSPHERIC LAYERS: 45,

[number][grid][rtflag] LAYER BOUNDARY LOCATIONS WITH FLAG:

   0         0.0  1 
   1      1000.0  1 
   2      2000.0  1 
   3      3000.0  1 
   4      4000.0  1 
   5      5000.0  1 
   6      6000.0  1 
